# Navigator Rebuild & Deploy Process

When the user asks to **rebuild**, **deploy**, or **serve fresh** the frontend, follow this sequence exactly.

## 1. Kill Orphan Processes

Ensure no old Next.js processes are serving stale content:

```bash
# Find and kill orphan next dev / next-server on port 3000
ps aux | grep -E 'next|node.*navigator/frontend' | grep -v grep
# Kill PIDs: next dev, next-server, and their parent sh
kill <pids>
ss -tlnp | grep 3000   # Verify port 3000 is free
```

## 2. Clear Cache & Rebuild

```bash
cd /opt/navigator/frontend
rm -rf .next
npm run build
```

## 3. Restart Navigator via PM2

```bash
pm2 delete navigator-frontend 2>/dev/null
cd /opt/navigator
pm2 start ecosystem.config.cjs --only navigator-frontend
pm2 save
```

## 4. Reload Nginx (NPM)

Ports 80/443 are used by **Nginx Proxy Manager** (Docker), not system nginx:

```bash
docker exec nginx_proxy_app_1 nginx -t && docker exec nginx_proxy_app_1 nginx -s reload
```

## 5. Verify

```bash
ss -tlnp | grep 3000
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://127.0.0.1:3000/
```

## Notes

- **Single frontend instance**: Only one Next.js process should listen on 3000. Kill orphans before starting.
- **Backend**: If backend needs restart: `pm2 reload navigator-backend`
- **User override**: If user explicitly asks to restart nginx, follow their instruction (they may override process-protection).
